Germany’s Roesler Says Taxes Are Too High, Bild Says

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-04-07T09:16:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/germany-s-roesler-says-taxes-are-too-high-bild-says.html
German Health Minister Philipp Roesler, who’s running to become leader of the Free Democratic
Party, said taxes in  Europe ’s biggest economy are too high and
should be lowered when there is leeway in the budget,  Bild 
newspaper reported, citing an interview.  Roesler also said while Germany had “good reasons” not to
participate in military action against the regime of Libyan
leader  Muammar Qaddafi , the country will participate in
humanitarian aid planned by the European Union.  Roesler is bidding to become leader of the FDP, Chancellor
Angela Merkel’s junior coalition partner, at a party convention
in May.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  